		<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>Sydney Royal Easter Show has vital influence in terms of economy and cultural exchange. Easter Day is one of the most ancient and consequential Christian festivals of all time. To celebrate the revival of Jesus Christ, different countries hold distinguished events every year.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>
 
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>To celebrate the Australian Culture and heritage, Royal Easter Show attracts over 800,000 visitors from all over the globe annually. This grand event is next only to the magnificent firework which takes place at the Harbor Bridge on New Year&rsquo;s Eve! &nbsp;Australians love celebrations and everything awesome will make them excited. In Royal Easter Show, there are endless activities you can participate at the show with family members and friends,&nbsp; including trying stimulating recreational facilities and unique local snacks, buying interesting show bags, visiting countless handicrafts stalls,&nbsp; petting cute animals and getting to know the finest agricultural products. Almost everyone&nbsp; can find their own cup of tea and it is going to be amazing experience for visitors from different backgrounds.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>Royal Easter Show will take place from March 17th to 30th in 2016. Our company would exert every effort to seize the incredible opportunity to diffuse Chinese traditional culture in Australia&nbsp; and strengthen cultural communication between the two countries.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<div><!-- [if ppt]--></div>
<div>
<p>For all the exhibitors，this is an incredible opportunity for the business development. Average expenditure per person reaches over $113 and average hour of the patrons staying at the show reaches 8 hours which guarantees a good source of customers and a great quantity of visitors. The event provides an excellent platform for the exhibitors to represent themselves and approximately 70% of the entities not only can realize their sales target but are dedicated to participating in the show every year. Royal Easter Show boosts communication between visitors and business owners as well as business cooperation between enterprises while enhances exhibitors&rsquo; popularity and publicity.</p>
</div>
<div>&nbsp;</div>
<div>
<p>In matter of employment, agriculture development, tourism, infrastructure and transportation, the show has an economic impact of over $500,000,000, including an estimated $24,500,000 attributed to interstate and international visitation from countries such as China, Hong Kong, Japan and Korea.</p>
</div>
<div>&nbsp;</div>
<div>
<p>The booth is located in Kids World with various recreational facilities and appealing exotic snacks which is most prevalent with families. We are proud to be the first company to demonstrate Chinese traditional arts and crafts with traditional culture in Australia at the show with sugar painting, sugar coating fruit sticks and fun pulling-sugar display and sales. We will also invite well-known artisans to be at our booth for traditional art demonstration.</p>
</div>
<div>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>Time: 17th March- 30th March, 2016</p>
<p>Location: <span class="_Xbe">1 Showground Rd, Sydney Olympic Park NSW 2127</span></p>
